│ The `trunc` instruction is used in the `narrowSDivOrSRem` and `narrowUDivOrURem`        │
│ functions to reduce the bitwidth of operands. These functions create truncated versions │
│ of the operands and then extend the result back to the original bitwidth. This          │
│ transformation assumes that the truncation does not introduce `poison` values.          │
│                                                                                         │
│ The test failure suggests that the `trunc` instruction in the transformation pipeline   │
│ may produce `poison` values, leading to undefined behavior. To address this, I will     │
│ modify the `narrowSDivOrSRem` and `narrowUDivOrURem` functions to ensure that the       │
│ operands are frozen before truncation. This will prevent the introduction of `poison`   │
│ values.                                                                                 │
